3.2 VULNERABILITY OVERVIEW
3.2.1 вЂ‹IMPROPER RESTRICTION OF EXCESSIVE AUTHENTICATION ATTEMPTS CWE-307В 
вЂ‹There is no limit on the number of login attempts. This could allow a brute force attack on the built-in web server login.В 
вЂ‹CVE-2023-40706 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 7.5 has been assigned; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N).В 
3.2.2 вЂ‹WEAK PASSWORD REQUIREMENTS CWE-521В 
вЂ‹There are no requirements for setting a complex password, which could allow a successful brute force attack if users don't setup complex credentials.В 
вЂ‹CVE-2023-40707 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 7.5 has been assigned; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N).В 
3.2.3 вЂ‹IMPROPER ACCESS CONTROL CWE-284В 
вЂ‹The File Transfer Protocol (FTP) port is open by default. This could allow an adversary to access some device files.В 
вЂ‹CVE-2023-40708 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 5.3 has been assigned; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:N).В 
3.2.4В UNCONTROLLED RESOURCE CONSUMPTION CWE-400В 
вЂ‹An adversary could crash the entire device by sending large quantity of ICMP requests if the controller has the built-in web server enabled but not completely set-up and configured.В 
вЂ‹CVE-2023-40709 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 5.9 has been assigned; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).В 
3.2.5 вЂ‹UNCONTROLLED RESOURCE CONSUMPTION CWE-400В 
вЂ‹An adversary could cause a continuous restart loop to the entire device by sending large quantity of HTTP GET requests if the controller has the built-in web server enabled but does not have the built-in web server completely set-up and configured.В 
вЂ‹CVE-2023-40710 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 5.9 has been assigned; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).В 
